[The suggestion that pigs may serve as useful sentinels for the presence of Zika virus circulation in an area where the presence of the virus is suspected or proven is interesting. One hopes that these observations will be tested in other geographic areas where the virus is being transmitted.

There are far fewer cases of Zika virus infection than in recent years. Some of this may be due to the overwhelming attention paid to the COVID-19 pandemic. Nonetheless, a few cases are confirmed currently. The virus has not gone away. Continued surveillance is warranted. - Mod.TY

